{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἀλλοι-όω</b>, <br /> (ἀλλοῖος) <b>change, alter</b>, φύσιν[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “παραγγελίαι” 9 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τροφὴν ἐς τὸ γάλα[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Gland.” 16, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 381a, etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>represent as</b> ἀλλοῖος (which see), [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.AD: Plotinus Philosophus 3.6.3. \">Refs 3rd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <i>passive</i>, <i>future</i> <b>-ωθήσομαι</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus “de Usu Partium” 8.6, etc., but -ώσομαι [prev. work] 10.1\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]:—<b>become different, be changed</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ διαίτης” 1.4, etc.; ἀλλοιοῦσθαι τὴν γνώμην 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.59; τῇ ὄψει 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Cynegeticus” 9.4\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἀλλοίωσιν ἀλλοιοῦσθαι <b>undergo an alteration</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Theaetetus” 181d\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; rare in Poetry, ὄλοιντ᾽ ἰδοῦσαι τούσδ᾽ ἂν ἠλλοιωμένους[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Supplices” 944. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <b>to be estranged</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd-3rd c.AD: Dio Cassius Historicus 37.11. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> <b>to be changed for the worse</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 3.3.9, 3rd c.BC: Euphro Comicus 10, LXX.Lam.4.1. \">LXX+5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.4</b></Level3> <b>to be confused in mind</b>, ὑπὸ τῆς μέθης[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 8.27.5. \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.5</